  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>your <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>ground paprika</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>smoky fries</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1678874307714-x200.jpg",
